# String-X Environment Configuration
#
# This file allows you to customize String-X behavior through environment variables.
# The notification system will automatically load these settings.

# Project root directory (alternative to auto-detection)
# Useful when String-X is installed in non-standard locations
STRINGX_PROJECT_ROOT=/mnt/dadosm2/Documentos/string-x

# Direct path to notification icon (takes precedence over PROJECT_ROOT + asset/icon.png)
# Set this to use a completely custom icon for desktop notifications
# STRINGX_ICON_PATH=/custom/path/to/icon.png

# Examples of custom icon paths:
# STRINGX_ICON_PATH=/mnt/dadosm2/Documentos/string-x/asset/logo.png
# STRINGX_ICON_PATH=/usr/share/icons/custom-strx-icon.png
# STRINGX_ICON_PATH=/home/user/.config/stringx/custom-icon.png

# Priority order for icon resolution:
# 1. STRINGX_ICON_PATH environment variable (if file exists)
# 2. STRINGX_PROJECT_ROOT/asset/icon.png (if PROJECT_ROOT set and file exists)  
# 3. Values from this .env file (if found)
# 4. Auto-detected project root + asset/icon.png (fallback)